## Promotion workflow

1. Confirm every station has a fresh sample.
2. Compare the release digest with the signed announcement.
3. Keep an observer free to read the raw event stream.
   - Record times in UTC.
   - Avoid interpreting transient retries.

::procedure-card{number="1" title="Prepare the window"}
---
owner: release-operator
duration_minutes: 10
requires:
  - signed digest
  - observer
---

#summary
Preparation should be quiet, reversible, and easy to narrate.

#default
Run the verifier from a clean checkout:

```shell
git fetch --tags origin
git verify-tag v7.4.0
./scripts/release-check --environment orbital
```

::callout{tone="warning" icon='pause'}
Do not promote when two adjacent receivers are stale. Ask
:person{handle="field-ops"}[field operations] to classify the outage first.
::

#actions
:button{command="verify" variant="solid"}[Run verification]
::

The component-local YAML frontmatter above is closed before its Markdown body.

:::procedure-card{number="2" title="Observe promotion"}
#summary
Watch two refresh cycles.

::::timeline{ordered=true}
:::::timeline-item{time="21:30" state="complete"}
The operator announces version `7.4.0` and the expected digest.
:::::

:::::timeline-item{time="21:32" state="active"}
The observer compares :kbd[observedAt] with :kbd[receivedAt] in the raw event.
:::::

:::::timeline-item{time="21:34" state="pending"}
The field lead records [promotion complete]{class='audit-label'} in the log.
:::::
::::

#aside
::note{tone="info"}
Normal queue movement may reorder stations for one refresh. A second sample
distinguishes expected movement from a persistent regression.
::
:::

## Evidence and links

The browser adapter narrows a response before rendering it:

```typescript
type Reading = {
  station: string
  observedAt: string
  lagSeconds: number
}

export function isFresh(reading: Reading): boolean {
  return reading.lagSeconds >= 0 && reading.lagSeconds < 90
}
```

